{
  "stem": "18778.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, the American consulates had been instructed, as we now know, not to make it too easy for people-- for Jews to enter the United States.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And since there-- the German quota for immigration into the States at that time was 25,000 per year, 25,000 people per year.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the government made no allowances barring from other quotas that was it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we now also have found out that those quotas were never even filled, even though at that time we didn't know it.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was such an onslaught for requests that then the consulate issued numbers, first come, first serve numbers, like in a delicatessen store.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was never an official announcement.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It spread over Germany by word of mouth.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know my parents had friends-- excuse me-- [DRINKS] with whom they got together regularly, who by very casual conversation said, well, there is now a quota system.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You have-- you have to get numbers in-- before you can go to the consulate.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Our consulate was in Stuttgart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "You have to apply for a number.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And immediately, my mother would call up her sister in Berlin and say, listen, you've got to get a number.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My parents had a fairly low number.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was-- I have the documentation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was in the 14,000s.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That was considered a low number.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "By the time her sister was able to get to a consulate and get a number, they were in the 70,000s.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that was like a condemnation to death.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And you could not-- you could not do anything without that number insofar as coming into the United States.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My-- my parents had an affidavit by the-- by the beginning of 1939, and they had visa.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
